    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "18. when they had called to the king—Hezekiah did not make a personal appearance, but commissioned his three principal ministers to meet the Assyrian deputies at a conference outside the city walls.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Eliakim—lately promoted to be master of the royal household (Isa 22:20).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Shebna—removed for his pride and presumption (Isa 22:15) from that office, though still royal secretary.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Joah … the recorder—that is, the keeper of the chronicles, an important office in Eastern countries.",
        "children": []
      }
